                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">7</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Incomplete Environment Variable Override System</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff6600;"><strong>HIGH</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">RemoteDB.pm lines 106-136</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">COMSERV_DB_* pattern requires file-based config first</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">8</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Multi-Connection Priority Lost in K8s</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff6600;"><strong>HIGH</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">db_config.json entire structure</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">10-entry priority system cannot be stored in flat Secrets</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">9</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Docker-Entrypoint Tests Incomplete</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff9800;"><strong>MEDIUM</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">docker-entrypoint.sh, t/docker-entrypoint_non_k8s.t</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">Migration fallback untested for K8s case</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">10</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);"><strong>Manual Secret Creation Process</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: #ff9800;"><strong>MEDIUM</strong></td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">DevOps process only</td>
                <td style="padding: var(--spacing-small); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); color: var(--text-color);">No automation from db_config.json → K8s Secret</td>
            </tr>
        </table>

        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Detailed Issue Breakdown</h3>

        <div style="background-color: #ffe3e3; border-left: 4px solid #d32f2f; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 1: db_config.json File-Based Authentication (CRITICAL)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Root Cause</strong>: The application architecture loads database credentials from db_config.json at module initialization time. DBSchemaManager.pm (lines 28-81) and RemoteDB.pm (lines 44-104) both use file-based config loading as the primary method.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Problem</strong>: In Kubernetes containers, files are ephemeral and overwritten on restart. Credentials should come from Secrets or environment variables, not files.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Symptoms</strong>: Application startup fails immediately with "Error loading config file: Could not open db_config.json"</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Files Affected</strong>:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>DBSchemaManager.pm (lines 28-81) - Dies if file not found</li>
                <li>RemoteDB.pm (lines 44-104) - Primary config loading</li>
                <li>docker-entrypoint.sh (lines 11-30) - Migration logic exists but incomplete</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Migration Path</strong>: Implement lazy-loading with fallback: (1) Try K8s Secrets first, (2) Try environment variables, (3) Only then try file, (4) Implement graceful degradation for non-K8s environments.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #ffe3e3; border-left: 4px solid #d32f2f; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #d32f2f; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 2 & 3: Hardcoded Credentials in Configuration Files (CRITICAL)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Locations</strong>:</p>
            <ul style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>docker-compose.dev.yml line 18: DB_PASS with actual password default</li>
                <li>.env.example: DB_PASSWORD, CONFIG_DB_PASSWORD with example credentials</li>
                <li>db_config.json lines 22, 34, 46, 58, 70, 82: Plain-text passwords repeated across all 10 connection configurations</li>
            </ul>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Risk</strong>: Credentials are in git history. Even if deleted, they remain in commit history and can be extracted by anyone with repository access.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Mitigation</strong>: (1) BFG Repo Cleaner to remove from history, (2) Rotate all exposed credentials, (3) Use .gitignore to prevent future exposure, (4) Use GitHub Secrets for all CI/CD.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff6600; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 4: Multiple Config File Path Resolution (HIGH)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Problem</strong>: RemoteDB.pm lines 58-71 check multiple paths in priority order:</p>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background: #f5f5f5; padding: 8px; margin: 8px 0;">Priority 1: /opt/comserv/db_config.json (Docker container)
Priority 2: $ENV{COMSERV_DB_CONFIG} (environment override)
Priority 3: $FindBin::Bin/../db_config.json (local development)</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Impact in K8s</strong>: If multiple containers have different paths or the file is partially mounted, they will load different configurations or fail silently with wrong credentials.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Standardize on environment variable (COMSERV_DB_CONFIG) and validate path exists before attempting load. Log which path was used.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff6600; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 5: Wrong Config Filename in ConfigDatabaseInit (HIGH)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location</strong>: ConfigDatabaseInit.pm lines 97-99</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Code</strong>: Searches for <code>dbi_config.json</code> but actual filename is <code>db_config.json</code></p>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background: #f5f5f5; padding: 8px; margin: 8px 0;">foreach my $path ('/opt/comserv/dbi_config.json', './dbi_config.json', ...)</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Impact</strong>: Config database initialization silently fails to import credentials because it's searching for the wrong filename.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Fix</strong>: Replace <code>dbi_config.json</code> with <code>db_config.json</code> in all three path checks.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff6600; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 6: DBSchemaManager Fatal on Missing Config (HIGH)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location</strong>: DBSchemaManager.pm lines 77-79</p>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background: #f5f5f5; padding: 8px; margin: 8px 0;">if ($@) {
    die "Error loading config file $config_file: $@";
}</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Problem</strong>: Module initialization uses die() which terminates the entire application during require/import. This prevents graceful fallback or startup in environments where db_config.json should not be required.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>K8s Impact</strong>: In Kubernetes with Secrets-only configuration, the module fails to load during app startup even though credentials are available via environment.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Make config loading lazy (on first use, not at module load). Implement Try::Tiny with fallback to environment variables.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff6600; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 7: Incomplete Environment Variable Override System (HIGH)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Location</strong>: RemoteDB.pm lines 106-136 (_apply_env_overrides method)</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Behavior</strong>: Environment variables (COMSERV_DB_*) only override connection parameters IF a file-based config is loaded first. Pattern requires the JSON config to exist for env vars to override values.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>K8s Problem</strong>: In pure K8s deployments with only Secrets (no json file), this override system never activates because there's nothing to override.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Implement two-tier config loading: (1) Build config from environment variables first (COMSERV_DB_* pattern), (2) If file exists, override those values with file values (for backwards compatibility).</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #fff3cd; border-left: 4px solid #ff6600; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff6600; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 8: Multi-Connection Priority System Cannot Be Stored in K8s Secrets (HIGH)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Architecture</strong>: db_config.json contains 10 connection configurations with priority levels (1=highest to 10=lowest fallback):</p>
            <pre style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: monospace; background: #f5f5f5; padding: 8px; margin: 8px 0;">1. production_server (Priority 1)
2. production_forager (Priority 2)
3. zerotier_ency (Priority 3)
4. zerotier_forager (Priority 4)
5. local_ency (Priority 5)
6. local_forager (Priority 6)
7. backup_ency (Priority 7)
8. backup_forager (Priority 8)
9. sqlite_ency (Priority 9)
10. sqlite_forager (Priority 10)</pre>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>K8s Limitation</strong>: Kubernetes Secrets are flat key-value stores. They cannot represent hierarchical priority systems or complex JSON structures.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Two approaches: (A) Store entire db_config.json as single base64-encoded Secret (docker-entrypoint.sh currently does this), or (B) Simplify to single "active" connection in K8s (removes fallback feature).</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 9: Docker-Entrypoint Tests Incomplete (MEDIUM)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Status</strong>: Test file <code>t/docker-entrypoint_non_k8s.t</code> exists and covers non-K8s fallback case. Missing: Test for successful K8s migration case.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Gap</strong>: No test verifies that when kubectl IS available and Secret creation succeeds, the db_config.json file is properly deleted and the Secret is actually created.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Create <code>t/docker-entrypoint_k8s.t</code> test that mocks kubectl, verifies Secret creation call, and confirms file deletion.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="background-color: #ffe6e6; border-left: 4px solid #ff9800; padding: var(--spacing-medium); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <h4 style="color: #ff9800; font-family: var(--header-font);">ISSUE 10: Manual Secret Creation Process (MEDIUM)</h4>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Current Process</strong>: DevOps must manually create K8s Secrets from db_config.json. No automated process exists.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Risk</strong>: Manual process is error-prone and undocumented. New deployments or updates require manual Secret management.</p>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Solution</strong>: Create automation script (shell or Perl) that: (1) Reads db_config.json, (2) Creates/updates K8s Secrets in current namespace, (3) Validates creation succeeded, (4) Can be run in CI/CD pipeline on each deployment.</p>
        </div>

        <h3 style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--header-font); font-size: var(--font-size-large); margin-top: var(--spacing-large);">Remediation Roadmap</h3>

        <div style="background-color: var(--light-color); padding: var(--spacing-medium); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); margin: var(--spacing-medium) 0;">
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Phase 0.5 (Immediate - Next 3 days)</strong>:</p>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Fix ISSUE 2 & 3: Remove hardcoded credentials from files, use placeholders or .env</li>
                <li>Fix ISSUE 5: Correct filename from dbi_config.json to db_config.json</li>
                <li>Complete ISSUE 9: Create docker-entrypoint_k8s.t test</li>
                <li>Create ISSUE 10: Automation script for Secret creation</li>
            </ol>
            <p style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);"><strong>Phase 1 (Next 2-3 weeks)</strong>:</p>
            <ol style="color: var(--text-color); font-family: var(--body-font);">
                <li>Fix ISSUE 1: Implement lazy-loading config with fallback chain</li>
                <li>Fix ISSUE 6: Convert die() to graceful fallback in DBSchemaManager</li>
